    "body": "When one adds run args or attach args in a run configuration that extend beyond the width of the screen they are hidden. Suggest changing the text box from single line to multiline.\r\n\r\nThe test configuration screen handles overflow a bit better, but multiline args here would be nice as well.\r\n\r\n## Steps to Reproduce\r\n\r\nType a bunch of args into a run configuration:\r\n<img width=\"1840\" alt=\"Screen Shot 2022-02-09 at 3 46 19 PM\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/817672/153303325-6bd72792-6f49-4607-8df2-2b9abe7a12f4.png\">\r\n\r\n\r\n## Version info\r\n\r\n```\r\n/opt/homebrew/Caskroom/flutter/2.5.3/flutter/bin/flutter doctor --verbose\r\n[âœ“] Flutter (Channel stable, 2.8.1, on macOS 12.1 21C52 darwin-arm, locale en-US)\r\n    â€¢ Flutter version 2.8.1 at /opt/homebrew/Caskroom/flutter/2.5.3/flutter\r\n    â€¢ Upstream repository https://github.com/flutter/flutter.git\r\n    â€¢ Framework revision 77d935af4d (8 weeks ago), 2021-12-16 08:37:33 -0800\r\n    â€¢ Engine revision 890a5fca2e\r\n    â€¢ Dart version 2.15.1\r\n\r\n[âœ“] Android toolchain - develop for Android devices (Android SDK version 31.0.0)\r\n    â€¢ Android SDK at /Users/spencerconnaughton/Library/Android/sdk\r\n    â€¢ Platform android-31, build-tools 31.0.0\r\n    â€¢ ANDROID_HOME = /Users/spencerconnaughton/Library/Android/sdk\r\n    â€¢ Java binary at: /Users/spencerconnaughton/Library/Application Support/JetBrains/Toolbox/apps/AndroidStudio/ch-0/211.7628.21.2111.8139111/Android Studio.app/Contents/jre/Contents/Home/bin/java\r\n    â€¢ Java version OpenJDK Runtime Environment (build 11.0.11+0-b60-7772763)\r\n    â€¢ All Android licenses accepted.\r\n\r\n[âœ“] Xcode - develop for iOS and macOS (Xcode 13.2.1)\r\n    â€¢ Xcode at /Applications/Xcode.app/Contents/Developer\r\n    â€¢ CocoaPods version 1.11.2\r\n\r\n[âœ“] Chrome - develop for the web\r\n    â€¢ Chrome at /Applications/Google Chrome.app/Contents/MacOS/Google Chrome\r\n\r\n[âœ“] Android Studio (